get.description:
This endpoint makes an HTTP GET request to retrieve information about a user in a specific school and school year. The request should include the school ID and the user ID in the URL parameters.

### Request
- `:schoolInSchoolYear` (path parameter) - The ID of the school in the specific school year.

- `:userId` (path parameter) - The ID of the user.
- `type=` (optional) - The type of user: student or teacher


### Response

The response will have a status code of 200 and a content type of application/json. The response body will include an array of user data, with fields such as code, first name, prefix, and last name.

Example response:

``` json
{
    "statusCode": 200,
    "message": "",
    "details": "",
    "rowCount": 1,
    "data": [
        {
            "code": "",
            "firstName": "",
            "prefix": "",
            "lastName": ""
        }
    ]
}

 ```

#### JSON Schema

``` json
{
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "statusCode": {
            "type": "number"
        },
        "message": {
            "type": "string"
        },
        "details": {
            "type": "string"
        },
        "rowCount": {
            "type": "number"
        },
        "data": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {
                "type": "object",
                "properties": {
                    "code": {
                        "type": "string"
                    },
                    "firstName": {
                        "type": "string"
                    },
                    "prefix": {
                        "type": "string"
                    },
                    "lastName": {
                        "type": "string"
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
}

 ```

This endpoint makes an HTTP GET request to retrieve appointments in the schedule of the given user. The request should include the userId in the URL parameters. Start and end are optional, otherwise the current week is given.

### Request

- `:userId` (path parameter) - The ID of the user (for example 545959 or GIJS)

- `start=` (optional) - UTC Unix time of the start of this appointment. This is the first second this appointment is taking place

- `end=` (optional) - UTC Unix time of the end of this appointment. This is the last second this appointment is taking place


### Response

The response will have a status code of 200 and a content type of `application/json`. The response body will include an array of user data, with fields such as code, first name, prefix, and last name.  
Example response:

``` json
{
    "statusCode": 200,
    "message": "",
    "details": "",
    "rowCount": 1,
    "data": [
        {
            "id": 0,
            "appointmentInstance": 0,
            "start": "",
            "end": "",
            "locations": [""],
            "subjects": [""],
            "teachers": [""]
        }
    ]
}

 ```

